            <paragraph>Shortcuts (also known as hotkeys) are containers of <reference internal="True" refuri="class_inputevent#class-inputevent"><inline classes="std std-ref">InputEvent</inline></reference> resources. They are commonly used to interact with a <reference internal="True" refuri="class_control#class-control"><inline classes="std std-ref">Control</inline></reference> element from an <reference internal="True" refuri="class_inputevent#class-inputevent"><inline classes="std std-ref">InputEvent</inline></reference>.</paragraph>
            <paragraph>One shortcut can contain multiple <reference internal="True" refuri="class_inputevent#class-inputevent"><inline classes="std std-ref">InputEvent</inline></reference> resources, making it possible to trigger one action with multiple different inputs.</paragraph>
            <paragraph><strong>Example:</strong> Capture the <literal classes="kbd">Ctrl + S</literal> shortcut using a <strong>Shortcut</strong> resource:</paragraph>
